DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
# "parserNumberWithUnits.pl",
# "parserFormulaWithUnits.pl", 
# "parserFormulaUpToConstant.pl",
# "PGcourse.pl",
);

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are( t=>'Real' );

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$r1 = list_random(2,3);
$r2 = ( $r1 == 3 ) ? 2 : 3;
$t0 = list_random(1,2,3);
$t1 = $t0 + random(2,6,1);

$int = Compute( "$t1^5 - $t0^5" );

Context()->texStrings;
TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT

Evaluate the line integral
\( \int_C y\, dx + x\, dy \) where \( C \)
is the parameterized path \( x = t^{$r1} \), \( y=t^{$r2} \),
\( $t0\le t \le $t1 \).

$PAR
\( \int_C y\, dx + x\, dy = \) \{ ans_rule(45) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( $int->cmp() );

$x = Compute( "t^($r1)" );
$dx = $x->D('t');
$y = Compute( "t^($r2)" );
$dy = $y->D('t');

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

From \(x=$x\) and \(y=$y\) we get \(dx = $dx\,dt\) and
\(dy = $dy\,dt\).  Hence
\[
\int_C y\,dx + x\,dy =
\int_{$t0}^{$t1}  $y ($dx)\, dt + $y ($dx)\, dt =
\int_{$t0}^{$t1}  5\,t^4\, dt = ($t1)^5 - ($t0)^5 = $int.
\]


END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
